{
  "stem": "24650.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after they killed the wife and husband, we were already to the right side.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My girlfriend came out with her daughter, three and 1/2 years old.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So three-- two Ukrainian SS-- because our ghetto [? closed ?] the Ukrainian SS, not the German-- took the child for both legs, in half, and up the wall.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was three and 1/2 years old.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The mother stayed alive.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were in [? chimney ?] together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We will get free together.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She just passed away this year.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I didn't say about my father.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "First of all, my father has written 500 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], a Torah.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It means not the Torah that we have now, but in the same, in the same style in Hebrew, about what's going on from the beginning up to the end before we left the ghetto, what's going on in the ghetto, what the Germans did, what the Jewish people did not [? right, ?] who got killed, why they got killed, everything.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they close it up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they took it to the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] in the, in the cellar.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When I was in '56, the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] was there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I came in '93, no more [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], a new house.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think this must be under the ground.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Doesn't matter.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I hope somebody will find, because there is written the date and his name and his family and the date when he finished.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So when he finished it, two or three days later, I took them to the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], to go out from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They wait for-- not for him, for many people-- to take him to [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he was Jewish, not another thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
